WEBVTT

00:02.690 --> 00:04.560
How much doubt...

00:04.560 --> 00:06.150
is reasoNable?

00:06.150 --> 00:08.900
Well, folks...

00:08.900 --> 00:10.740
if I had To choose

00:10.740 --> 00:14.280
whether or not
to take someone's life...

00:14.280 --> 00:16.120
and that is the choice
Before you today,

00:16.120 --> 00:18.740
make no mistake...

00:18.740 --> 00:21.870
I don't think any amount
would seem reasonable.

00:21.870 --> 00:25.000
Now, me, I had to kill someone,

00:25.000 --> 00:28.040
I'd need it etched in gold
and signed by God Himself.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.800
So I ask...

00:32.630 --> 00:34.880
how much doubt
are you folks comfortable with?

00:38.010 --> 00:40.100
<i>He tells me a story...</i>

00:40.100 --> 00:44.230
<i>He says he's my son, Henry.
Adopted.</i>

00:44.230 --> 00:46.400
Did you start

00:46.400 --> 00:48.650
the fire in the hospital?

00:48.650 --> 00:51.360
<i>And then he starts in:
"I heard it, Dad."</i>

00:52.650 --> 00:54.700
We have to go.
To the woods.

00:54.700 --> 00:56.780
The schisma has been
getting louder again, Henry.

00:56.780 --> 00:58.620
<i>It hasn't risen to these levels</i>

00:58.620 --> 01:00.540
<i>in decades.</i>

01:00.540 --> 01:02.290
Do you hear it?

01:03.660 --> 01:04.830
We have to go...

01:04.830 --> 01:06.000
We have to go to the woods.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.330
Who are you?

01:07.330 --> 01:10.550
<i>The reason, the stain,</i>

01:10.550 --> 01:12.760
<i>the curse on our town,</i>

01:12.760 --> 01:15.130
<i>dragging evil behind you
everywhere you went.</i>

01:15.130 --> 01:17.090
<i>I was trying to get back.</i>

01:17.090 --> 01:19.850
<i>I couldn't.
Then Lacy found me.</i>

01:19.850 --> 01:22.350
<i>Took me to Shawshank.</i>

01:22.350 --> 01:24.020
<i>But after all these years...</i>

01:24.020 --> 01:26.560
<i>I still don't know
what you really are.</i>

01:26.560 --> 01:28.150
You believe me, don't you?

